                       Third-Party Notices
------------------------------------------------------------------------

DeskAgent depends on a number of third-party libraries. The following
list highlights the major direct dependencies and their licenses. A
complete, up-to-date list of all transitive dependencies and their
license texts can be generated using the helper script
`scripts/collect_licenses.py` and is shipped with binary distributions.

  Anthropic Python SDK (anthropic)            MIT
  Google GenAI SDK (google-genai)             Apache 2.0
  OpenAI Python (openai)                      Apache 2.0
  Model Context Protocol SDK (mcp)            MIT
  FastAPI                                     MIT
  Uvicorn                                     BSD-3-Clause
  Pydantic                                    MIT
  pypdf                                       BSD-3-Clause
  openpyxl                                    MIT
  pywin32                                     PSF
  pystray                                     LGPLv3
  Pillow                                      HPND
  requests                                    Apache 2.0
  keyboard                                    MIT

Optional extras (installed via `pip install deskagent[<extra>]`):

  [anonymizer]
    presidio-analyzer                         MIT
    presidio-anonymizer                       MIT
    spaCy                                     MIT

  [claude-sdk]
    claude-agent-sdk                          MIT
    (note: bundles a proprietary `claude.exe` binary from Anthropic;
     not installed by default for this reason)

------------------------------------------------------------------------
                       AGPL-3.0 Compatibility
------------------------------------------------------------------------

All direct dependencies listed above are compatible with AGPL-3.0:

- MIT, BSD, Apache 2.0, PSF, HPND: permissive, can be combined with
  AGPL code without imposing additional obligations on the AGPL parts.
- LGPLv3 (pystray): explicitly compatible with AGPLv3 per the GNU
  License Compatibility Matrix. In source distributions and pip
  installs, pystray is loaded dynamically, preserving its LGPL
  obligations independently.

If you find a license-compatibility issue with a current or future
dependency, please report it via GitHub Issues or to info@realvirtual.io.
